snippet.textDisplay: I love the double entendre of the line “I’m watching my pupils as they get cornier.” In one aspect, he’s watching people who use his music as an example get cornier. On the other hand, he is watching (seeing through) the pupil of his own eye as it develops cornea disease (a common eye disease for people as they age)
